---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Traditional Clothing" description="Explore Chinese traditional clothing - hanfu, cheongsam, silk, and the art of Chinese fashion">
  
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="relative h-[70vh] flex items-center overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0">
      <img
        src="/images/hanfu.jpg"
        alt="Traditional Chinese clothing hanfu"
        class="w-full h-full object-cover"
      />
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-[#1a1a1a]/95 to-[#8E4585]/60"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="relative max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-2xl">
        <span class="inline-block font-heading text-sm tracking-[0.3em] text-[#D4AF37] mb-4">FASHION</span>
        <h1 class="font-display text-5xl md:text-6xl text-white mb-6">Traditional Clothing</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-stone-300 leading-relaxed">
          From the flowing elegance of hanfu to the sleek sophistication of the qipao, discover China's rich textile heritage.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Hanfu Section -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-[#FFFEF7]">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
        <div>
          <span class="inline-block font-heading text-sm tracking-[0.3em] text-[#C41E3A] mb-4">HERITAGE</span>
          <h2 class="font-display text-4xl text-[#1a1a1a] mb-6">Hanfu: The Ancient Way</h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-stone-600 mb-6">
            Hanfu (汉服) literally means "Han clothing" — the traditional attire of the Han Chinese people worn for over 3,000 years before the Qing Dynasty. Today, a vibrant revival movement is bringing this elegant clothing back to daily life.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-stone-600 mb-6">
            Characterized by its flowing robes, crossed collars (y领), and sash belts, hanfu represents principles of naturalness, restraint, and elegance that define classical Chinese aesthetics.
          </p>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-4">
            <div class="text-center p-4 bg-pink-50 rounded-lg">
              <div class="stat-number text-2xl">3000+</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-stone-600">Years of History</div>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center p-4 bg-pink-50 rounded-lg">
              <div class="stat-number text-2xl">6</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-stone-600">Core Elements</div>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center p-4 bg-pink-50 rounded-lg">
              <div class="stat-number text-2xl">4M+</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-stone-600">Modern Wearers</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="relative">
          <img
            src="/images/hanfu.jpg"
            alt="Woman in traditional hanfu"
            class="rounded-xl shadow-2xl"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Clothing Types -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-[#1a1a1a]">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <span class="inline-block font-heading text-sm tracking-[0.3em] text-[#D4AF37] mb-4">STYLES</span>
        <h2 class="font-display text-4xl text-white mb-4">Traditional Styles</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        {[
          {
            name: 'Magua',
            desc: 'A formal jacket worn over robes, traditionally by scholars and officials. Features a distinctive round collar and horse-hoof sleeves.',
            era: 'Ming Dynasty',
            color: 'bg-pink-600'
          },
          {
            name: 'Zhongyi',
            desc: 'A type of deep-robed garment with full sleeves and flowing lines, representing classical Chinese elegance.',
            era: 'Tang Dynasty',
            color: 'bg-rose-600'
          },
          {
            name: 'Curtain Dress (Lianshi)',
            desc: 'Features flowing skirts and elaborate draping. Popular among nobility during the Song Dynasty.',
            era: 'Song Dynasty',
            color: 'bg-purple-600'
          },
          {
            name: 'Shan (Upper Garment)',
            desc: 'A cross-collared upper garment that forms the foundation of many hanfu styles. Simple yet elegant.',
            era: 'Han Dynasty',
            color: 'bg-violet-600'
          }
        ].map(style => (
          <div class="bg-stone-800/50 border border-stone-700 rounded-xl overflow-hidden hover:border-pink-500 transition-colors">
            <div class={`h-2 ${style.color}`}></div>
            <div class="p-6">
              <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
                <h3 class="font-display text-2xl text-white">{style.name}</h3>
                <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-stone-700 text-stone-300 text-sm rounded-full">{style.era}</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-stone-400">{style.desc}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Silk -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-[#FFFEF7]">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <span class="inline-block font-heading text-sm tracking-[0.3em] text-[#C41E3A] mb-4">MATERIAL</span>
        <h2 class="font-display text-4xl text-[#1a1a1a] mb-4">The Golden Thread: Silk</h2>
      </div>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <div class="md:col-span-2">
          <img
            src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1558171813-4c088753af8f?w=800&q=80"
            alt="Silk fabric traditional Chinese textile"
            class="rounded-xl shadow-xl w-full h-80 object-cover"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <p class="text-lg text-stone-600">
            For over 3,000 years, China held the secret of silk production as a state secret — punishable by death if revealed. The Silk Road transformed trade and culture across Asia and Europe.
          </p>
          <div class="p-6 bg-[#D4AF37]/10 rounded-xl">
            <h4 class="font-display text-lg text-[#1a1a1a] mb-2">Silk Types</h4>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-stone-600">
              <li>• Satin — smooth, glossy finish</li>
              <li>• Brocade — raised patterns</li>
              <li>• Chiffon — lightweight, sheer</li>
              <li>• Organza — crisp, transparent</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gradient-to-r from-[#8E4585] to-[#C41E3A]">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 text-center">
      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl text-white mb-4">Continue Exploring</h2>
      <p class="text-white/80 text-lg mb-8">
        Discover how traditional clothing connects to poetry, art, and philosophy.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
        <a href="/" class="px-6 py-3 bg-white text-[#8E4585] font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-stone-100 transition-colors">
          Back to Home
        </a>
        <a href="/poetry" class="px-6 py-3 border border-white text-white font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-white/10 transition-colors">
          Explore Poetry
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
